**Step 1: Compute the time for the biggest slide**

- Length of biggest slide = 300 ft  
- Speed on biggest slide = 60 ft/min  

\[
\text{Time}_{\text{biggest}} = \frac{\text{Length}}{\text{Speed}}
= \frac{300\ \text{ft}}{60\ \text{ft/min}}
= 5\ \text{minutes}
\]

---

**Step 2: Compute the time for the second biggest slide**

- Length of second biggest slide = 240 ft  
- Speed on second biggest slide = 80 ft/min  

\[
\text{Time}_{\text{second}} = \frac{240\ \text{ft}}{80\ \text{ft/min}}
= 3\ \text{minutes}
\]

---

**Step 3: Find the difference in time**

\[
\text{Difference} = \text{Time}_{\text{biggest}} - \text{Time}_{\text{second}}
= 5\ \text{min} - 3\ \text{min}
= 2\ \text{minutes}
\]

---

**Answer: 2**

