**Step 1: Calculate the bus’s distance**

- Speed of the bus = 60 miles per hour  
- Time the bus travels = 5 hours  

\[
\text{Distance}_{\text{bus}} = \text{speed} \times \text{time}
= 60 \text{ mph} \times 5 \text{ h}
= 300 \text{ miles}
\]

---

**Step 2: Calculate the car’s distance**

- Speed of the car = 30 miles per hour  
- Time the car travels = 8 hours  

\[
\text{Distance}_{\text{car}} = 30 \text{ mph} \times 8 \text{ h}
= 240 \text{ miles}
\]

---

**Step 3: Find how much farther the bus went**

\[
\text{Difference} = \text{Distance}_{\text{bus}} - \text{Distance}_{\text{car}}
= 300 \text{ miles} - 240 \text{ miles}
= 60 \text{ miles}
\]

---

**Answer: 60**

